data.enText: forming an angle of 90˚ with another line or surface; vertical and going straight up
Are the lines perpendicular to each other?
The staircase was almost perpendicular (= very steep) .

data.chText: 垂直式的（英国14、15世纪盛行的建筑风格，以使用垂直线和大拱为特征）
data.enText: connected with a style of architecture common in England in the 14th and 15th centuries, that makes use of vertical lines and wide arches
a line, position or direction that is exactly perpendicular
The wall is a little out of the perpendicular.

word_means: 垂直式的(英国14、15世纪盛行的建筑风格，以使用垂直线和大拱为特征)
simple_means.memory_skill: per 自始至终 + pend 悬挂 + icular 有…性质的 → 始终挂着 → 垂直的

means: 垂直式的(英国14、15世纪盛行的建筑风格，以使用垂直线和大拱为特征)

tr: a cord from which a metal weight is suspended pointing directly to the earth's center of gravity
used to determine the vertical from a given point
a Gothic style in 14th and 15th century England
characterized by vertical lines and a four-centered (Tudor) arch and fan vaulting
a straight line at right angles to another line

example: the great perpendicular face of the cliff

tr: at right angles to the plane of the horizon or a base line
example: the monument consists of two vertical pillars supporting a horizontal slab

tr: intersecting at or forming right angles
example: the axes are perpendicular to each other

value.def: A perpendicular line or surface points straight up, rather than being sloping or horizontal.

example.ex: We made two slits for the eyes and a perpendicular line for the nose...
example.tran: 我们划了两道缝儿做眼睛,另外划了一条竖线做鼻子。

example.ex: The sides of the loch are almost perpendicular.

value.def: If one thing is perpendicular to another, it is at an angle of 90 degrees to it.

example.ex: The left wing dipped until it was perpendicular to the ground.
example.tran: 左翼下垂至与地面成90度角。
